  <brief_title>Unexcitability Along the Ablation as an Endpoint for Atrial Fibrillation Ablation</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Universitätsklinikum Hamburg-Eppendorf</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Universitätsklinikum Hamburg-Eppendorf</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study was to assess the near-term (12 months) efficacy of pulmonary vein
      isolation using a standard approach compared to application of an additional acute procedural
      endpoint of unexcitability along the ablation line.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
